ZCZC GE03
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 282300 UTC
LOW PRESSURE 991 WILL BE SITUATED TO THE SW OF THE UK ON THURSDAY EVENING
WITH ITS ASSOCIATED FRONTAL SYSTEM EXTENDING NWARDS ACROSS THE UK. THE LOW
PRESSURE 999 WILL MOV E INTO THE N SEA AS A FLN FEATURE OVERNIGHT AND INTO
FRIDAY MORNING WHICH WILL ALLOW A TRANSIENT RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE TO BUILD
FM THE W ACROSS THE UK DURING FRIDAY. MEANWHILE A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE
955 WILL BE SITUATED OVER THE MID-ATLANTIC ON SATURDAY AND SUNDAY. THIS IS
LIKELY TO BRING A SLOW MOV FRONTAL SYSTEM S-EWARDS ACROSS THE UK OVER THE
WEEKEND ALTHOUGH WITH SOME UNCERTAINTY AT THIS STAGE. STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY
ACROSS SERN CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS DURING FRIDAY MORNING BEFORE EASING THROUGH
THE DAY. FURTHER STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY ACROSS NERN CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS
DURING SATURDAY AND SUNDAY WITH THE RISK OF GALES ESPECIALLY FAIR ISLE
